    {
      "id": "PopularPost371610",
      "post_content": "@sir\\_dwar: I agree. Obviously all sorceries are better if made instants, but the slower speed is a balancing factor.   \n  \nThat said, this card honestly isn't likely to see a whole lot of yes. 1 discard for two mana, and not even randomized discard or [distress](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=distress) is simply underwhelming. The majority of starting hands has 1 or 2 cards that don't belong in an early game hand, which is exactly what will be discarded by this.  \n  \nBy the Time you were to hit 6 mana in a black deck (assuming you don't have mana-ramp, something that is uncommon but possible in black), your opponent will almost certainly have less than 4 cards in his hand, and probably will only have 1 or 2 he is simply waiting to dump.  \n  \nAlthough, decks that rely on frequent draws, Multiplayer matches where people are hesitant to summon things, or mana-ramp decks could make some use of this.",
      "posted_by": "Burningsickle",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost371610\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl03_post\">@sir_dwar: I agree. Obviously all sorceries are better if made instants, but the slower speed is a balancing factor. <br/><br/>That said, this card honestly isn't likely to see a whole lot of yes. 1 discard for two mana, and not even randomized discard or <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"distress\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=distress\">distress</a> is simply underwhelming. The majority of starting hands has 1 or 2 cards that don't belong in an early game hand, which is exactly what will be discarded by this.<br/><br/>By the Time you were to hit 6 mana in a black deck (assuming you don't have mana-ramp, something that is uncommon but possible in black), your opponent will almost certainly have less than 4 cards in his hand, and probably will only have 1 or 2 he is simply waiting to dump.<br/><br/>Although, decks that rely on frequent draws, Multiplayer matches where people are hesitant to summon things, or mana-ramp decks could make some use of this.</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl03_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl03_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '371610'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy66042\">Burningsickle</span>\r\n                                (4/22/2014 5:5